						Transfer Grammar 2.4.3 
						-----------------------
Transfer Grammar : 

Requirements:
------------
Operating System		:    LINUX/UNIX system

Compiler/Interpreter/Librarie(s):    Perl and SSF API's

For installation on Linux, please refer to the file INSTALL.

Directory Structure:
--------------------

transfergrammar
     |
     |---src (functional source code of the transfergrammar)
     |    
     |---data_bin (data bin files)
     |     |
     |     |---Rules (Transfer Rules)
     |	  
     |---API (SSF API's)
     |
     |---tests (contains the referenece input and output)
     |
     |---doc (documentation of the transfergrammar rules specification)
     |
     |---README (How to run/use the module)
     |
     |---INSTALL (How to install in sampark directory structure)
     |
     |---ChangeLog (version information)
     |
     |---Makefile (first level make file for copying the module source in sampark system)
     |
     |---Makefile.stage2 (2nd level make file for actual installation/copying in the bin and data_bin directory)
     |
     |---transfergrammar_run.sh (to run the transfergrammar module)
     |
     |---transfergrammar_train.sh (to train the transfergrammar module)
     |
     |---transfergrammar.sh (for the use of dashboard spec file)
     |
     |---transfergrammar.spec (individual transfergrammar module runs with dashboard)
     |
     |---transfergrammar.pl (main file of transfergrammar)



